Sekolah Menengah Sains Sultan Mohamad Jiwa (English: Sultan Mohamad Jiwa Science School; abbreviated SMSSMJ) is a boarding school in Malaysia funded by the Government of Malaysia. Named after the nineteenth reigning Sultan of Kedah, Almarhum Kebawah Duli Yang Maha Mulia Sultan Mohamad Jiwa Zainal Adilin II.
The school is located in Jalan Badlishah, Sungai Petani, Kedah. The school is widely known as Mad Jiwa.
In 2013, Sekolah Menengah Sains Sultan Mohamad Jiwa has 800 boys and 786 girls, bringing the total of 1775 students. It has a total number of 126 teachers.


